IBADAN – A lawmaker representing Iseyin/Itesiwaju/Kajola/Iwajowa federal constituency at the lower chamber of the National Assembly, Hon Shina Peller, has described the signing into law of the electoral act amendment Bill 2022 by President Muhammadu Buhari as victory for Nigerians. The federal legislator, who made this known via his personal social media platforms on Sunday, also described the development as a milestone achievement for the ninth Assembly, whilst he commended all who contributed immensely to making it a reality. Moreover,  Hon Peller noted that the new electoral law signifies hope for Nigerian youths and charged them to leverage on it in taking responsibility to choose their leaders in the forthcoming general election. Liverpool Win Carabao Cup Group Alleges Smear Campaign Against Akpabio In addition,  he urged the young ones to take action and get involved in the electoral process, adding that now is the time for those who are yet to get their PVCs to do so. The post read: “Yet another milestone for the 9th Assembly and a victory for Nigerians, as President Buhari signs into law, the electoral act amendment bill 2022. We now have a legal framework for the 2023 elections. I salute those who have remained dodged in pursuing this reality. “The signing of the electoral act 2022 signals hope for the youths to take responsibility to choose their leaders in the next election. I encourage those yet to get their PVC to do so in good time. Let’s take Action and Get Involved in Electoral Process Now. It’s Youth O’clock.”